                      /
                      <span>15</span>
                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2001-07-12</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>My title says it all. This is one of those "hand wave across the map" kind of books, and to call it a textbook is doing it quite a favor. If that's what you're into - a lot of dreams with no technical info to back it up, this book - and the most recent Starfleet manual - are for you. If you genuinely want to learn about real subjects in the area of high performance computing and networking, tho, skip this thing with prejudice.</span>
                  
              
